{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17620398","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17620398"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T15:42:00+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T15:42:00+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16625"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16625","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16625"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.16,0.19,0.03,0.05,0.57]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9316"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75903"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9316","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9316"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16625"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61416"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4937"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5116"},{"type":"tags","id":"5251"},{"type":"tags","id":"5317"},{"type":"tags","id":"10106"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22089"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22382"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75903","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/75903"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EMedications that block or modify oestrogen receptor function are important in treating hormone-sensitive cancers and other conditions.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the mechanism of action of selective oestrogen receptor modulators (SERMs)?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Selectively modulates oestrogen receptor expression in cell nuclei","Competitively inhibits aromatase to modulate oestrogen production","Selectively modulates oestrogen synthesis in ovarian tissue","Selectively antagonises oestrogen receptor beta subtypes","Acts as both an oestrogen receptor agonists and antagonists depending on tissue type"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003ESelective oestrogen receptor modulators (SERMs) \u003Cstrong\u003Eact as both oestrogen receptor agonists and antagonists depending on tissue type\u003C/strong\u003E. For example, tamoxifen acts as an antagonist at oestrogen receptors in in breast tissue (useful for treating breast cancer), and as an agonist in bone (helping prevent osteoporosis).\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESelectively modulates oestrogen receptor expression in cell nuclei\u003C/strong\u003E describes a mechanism more similar to pure oestrogen receptor antagonists like fulvestrant.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECompetitively inhibits aromatase to modulate oestrogen production\u003C/strong\u003E is the mechanism of aromatase inhibitors like anastrozole.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESelectively modulates oestrogen synthesis in ovarian tissue\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as SERMs act directly on oestrogen receptors rather than affecting hormone synthesis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESelectively blocks oestrogen receptor beta subtypes\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as SERMs act on both alpha and beta receptor subtypes.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe tissue-specific effects of SERMs depend on the presence of different coregulator proteins that interact with the oestrogen receptor complex in different tissues.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Selective oestrogen receptor modulators (SERMs) act as oestrogen receptor antagonists in breast tissue but agonists in bone.","Tamoxifen, a SERM, is used in oestrogen receptor positive breast cancer treatment and prevention.","Selective oestrogen down regulators (SERDs) such as fulvestrant act as antagonists in all tissues containing oestrogen receptors."],"references":["Therapeutic Guidelines. Melbourne: Therapeutic Guidelines Limited. Available from: https://www.tg.org.au","Ritter J, Flower RJ (Rod J), Henderson G (Graeme), et al.\u00a0Rang and Dale\u2019s Pharmacology. Tenth edition. Elsevier; 2024.","Australian Medicines Handbook\u00a0(online). Adelaide: Australian Medicines Handbook Pty Ltd. Available from:\u00a0https://amhonline.amh.net.au/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61416"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16625"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"61416","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/61416"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-01T13:10:38+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-01T13:11:06+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9316"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"75903"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGro